ract more users and engage them longer on your website. This user engagement is also good for your website&#8217;s search engine rankings. In this article, we&#8217;ve hand-picked the best WordPress poll plugins for you. How to Find the Best [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/7-best-wordpress-poll-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress Poll Plugins to Grow Onsite Engagement</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12359:\"<p>Do you want the best poll plugin to add online polls in WordPress? Polls and surveys attract more users and engage them longer on your website. This user engagement is also good for your website&#8217;s search engine rankings. </p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ve hand-picked the best WordPress poll plugins for you.</p>\n<h3>How to Find the Best WordPress Poll Plugin</h3>\n<p>WordPress has many free and paid poll plugins you can use to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/create-a-survey-in-wordpress/\">create online polls and surveys</a> on your website. When looking for a WordPress poll plugin, you should make sure that it can be easy to install and use. Other than that, it should be flexible with the display options so you can add the poll in your WordPress pages, posts, and widget areas.</p>\n<p>Here are a few quick features that you should look into a WordPress poll plugin before opting it for your website:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It should have design and styling features to create interactive polls.</li>\n<li>Make sure that the polls should load quickly and shouldn&#8217;t impact the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-caching-plugins-compared/\">performance of your website</a>.</li>\n<li>It should offer multiple options to show the poll and survey results like graphs, charts, etc.</li>\n<li>The poll plugin should allow you to display results on multiple pages or anywhere you like.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Having said that, let&#8217;s take a look at our side by side comparison of the best WordPress poll plugins.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"WPForms\">1. WPForms</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"WPForms\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"WPForms\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222076\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wpforms-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WPForms is the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\" title=\"7 Best WordPress Contact Form Plugins Compared (2018)\">best WordPress contact form plugin</a> in the world. It offers premium form templates to create contact forms, online registration forms, surveys, and polls in WordPress. WPForms has a premium addon for polls and surveys. Their online polls are highly customizable and flexible which means you can easily create a poll of your choice.</p>\n<p>WPForms has an amazing form builder that allows you to quickly create your online polls with the drag and drop functionality. You can also add images as poll option for users.</p>\n<p>You can display the online polls in your WordPress pages, posts, sidebar, and other widget-ready areas. Their polls shouldn&#8217;t affect the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-caching-plugins-compared/\">speed and performance</a> of your website.</p>\n<p>It allows you to display the poll results beautifully in graphs and charts. WPForms gives you the access to embed poll results anywhere on your WordPress website. You can also export the poll results and use them in your PowerPoint presentations, Excel Sheets, and more. For more details, you should check out this guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/create-a-survey-in-wordpress/\">how to create an interactive poll using WPForms</a>.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/polldaddy/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"PollDaddy Polls and Ratings\" rel=\"nofollow\">2. PollDaddy Polls and Ratings</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/polldaddy/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"PollDaddy Polls and Ratings\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/polldaddy.jpg\" alt=\"PollDaddy Polls and Ratings\" width=\"775\" height=\"395\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222148\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/polldaddy.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/polldaddy-300x153.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/polldaddy-768x391.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>PollDaddy is one of the most popular WordPress poll plugins in the market. It comes with flexible options to add and manage polls in WordPress. PollDaddy is easy to install and offer premium features for online polls.</p>\n<p>The most notable features include multiple choice poll, interactive poll designs, close date option for polls, show/hide results, and much more. Like any other powerful online poll plugin, you can display the poll results anywhere on your website and also on other WordPress sites.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/polldaddy/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"PollDaddy\" rel=\"nofollow\">PollDaddy</a> is a free <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-plugins/\">WordPress plugin</a> and supports basic IP filters to prevent users from filling multiple responses.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/poll-wp/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Responsive Poll\" rel=\"nofollow\">3. Responsive Poll</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/poll-wp/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Responsive Poll\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/responsivepoll.jpg\" alt=\"Responsive poll\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222147\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/responsivepoll.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/responsivepoll-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/responsivepoll-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Responsive poll is an online poll plugin that can be used to add simple and beautiful polls in WordPress. It allows you to create multiple polls and display them on the same page.</p>\n<p>You can also add multi-choice polls, image choices with text, display results beautifully, add polls start/end date, and customize your poll designs.</p>\n<p>They offer a free and paid version. The free Responsive Poll plugin has limited features and you need to upgrade to their premium plan to unlock all the options.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-polls/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"WP-Polls\" rel=\"nofollow\">4. WP-Polls</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wp-polls/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"WP-Polls\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wppolls.jpg\" alt=\"WP polls\" width=\"775\" height=\"390\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222145\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wppolls.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wppolls-300x151.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/wppolls-768x386.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WP-Polls is a free WordPress poll plugin suitable to add online polls in your website pages, posts, sidebar, and other widget areas. It&#8217;s easy to set up and use on your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>It allows you to add multiple choice polls and display results quickly on the same page. You can add custom CSS style to change the theme and design of your WordPress polls.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/democracy-poll/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Democracy Poll\" rel=\"nofollow\">5. Democracy Poll</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/democracy-poll/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Democracy Poll\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/democracypoll.jpg\" alt=\"Democracy poll\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222144\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/democracypoll.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/democracypoll-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/democracypoll-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As the name suggests, Democracy Poll is a simple and modern WordPress poll plugin that allows your users to add their own choices in the poll. You can create single and multiple choices polls, set an end date for your poll, choose from multiple poll design templates, and alot more.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s a highly customizable poll plugin and allows you to limit the poll to registered users only. Democracy Poll allows you to create random polls and display them to users on multiple pages.</p>\n<p>It works great with all the popular cache plugins like <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/w3-cache/\" title=\"W3 Total Cache\">W3 Total Cache</a>, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wp-super-cache/\" title=\"WP Super Cache Review 2018: Is It the Best WordPress Caching Plugin?\">WP Super Cache</a>, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/wordfence-security/\" title=\"WordFence Security\">WordFence</a>, Quick Cache, and more to perform faster on your website.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/yop-poll/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"YOP Poll\" rel=\"nofollow\">6. YOP Poll</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/yop-poll/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"YOP Poll\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoppoll.jpg\" alt=\"Yop Poll\" width=\"775\" height=\"400\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222142\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoppoll.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoppoll-300x155.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoppoll-768x396.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>YOP poll is another free WordPress poll plugin that can be used to easily create online polls and surveys. It&#8217;s super flexible and easy to set up in WordPress.</p>\n<p>It allows you to add multi-choice polls, schedule polls, show online polls on different pages, display results in percentages, reset the poll anytime, and add a limit to display polls to the registered users only. You can also block the spam users with IPs and username.</p>\n<p>They offer various options to display poll results. If you want to display previous poll results to users, then YOP poll is the perfect choice for you.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/social-polls-by-opinionstage/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"OpinionStage Poll, Survey, Quiz\" rel=\"nofollow\">7. OpinionStage Poll, Survey, Quiz</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/social-polls-by-opinionstage/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"OpinionStage Poll, Survey, Quiz\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/opinionstagepoll.jpg\" alt=\"OpinionStage Poll Survey Quiz\" width=\"775\" height=\"390\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222141\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/opinionstagepoll.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/opinionstagepoll-300x151.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/opinionstagepoll-768x386.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>OpinionStage Poll is an interactive poll plugin. It&#8217;s free to download and install on your WordPress website. You can easily create online polls, surveys, quizzes, forms, and more with their built-in templates.</p>\n<p>It comes with the social buttons alongside the polls to share them on your social media platforms. You can add the poll in your WordPress pages, posts, sidebar, footer, and other widget-ready areas.</p>\n<p>If you want to create a visually interactive poll in WordPress, then OpinionStage Poll is the perfect choice for you. They offer multiple color and design options to beautify the look of your online poll.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you find best WordPress poll plugins. You should also check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-survey-plugins-compared/\" title=\"10 Best WordPress Survey Plugins to Collect User Feedback (Compared)\">best WordPress survey plugins to collect user feedback</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/7-best-wordpress-poll-plugins/\">7 Best WordPress Poll Plugins to Grow Onsite Engagement</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://www.isitwp.com/7-best-wordpress-poll-plugins/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"SearchWP Review: Is It the Best WordPress Search Plugin?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/searchwp/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/searchwp/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 19 Sep 2018 14:30:14 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?post_type=isitwp_plugin&p=1187\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:599:\"<p>Are your visitors frustrating by irrelevant results when searching your site? The default WordPress search feature is so basic, it’s probably not indexing all the content your visitors are searching for. In our SearchWP review, find out how this plugin can power up your search and give your visitors the results they need.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/searchwp/\">SearchWP Review: Is It the Best WordPress Search Plugin?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14460:\"<p>Are your visitors frustrated by irrelevant results when searching your site? The default WordPress search feature is so basic, it can&#8217;t possibly index all of the content your visitors are searching for. In our <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> review, find out how this plugin can power up your search function and give your visitors the results they need.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1189\" src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review.png\" alt=\"SearchWP Review\" width=\"598\" height=\"192\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review.png 598w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-300x96.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 598px) 100vw, 598px\" /></a></p>\n<h3>Why You Need SearchWP</h3>\n<p>For a very basic WordPress blog, the built-in search feature might be enough.</p>\n<p>But, as WordPress has grown in popularity, basic blogs are in the minority. Now that WordPress is considered a full CMS (content management system), it’s used for all varieties of sites with all kinds of content.</p>\n<p>If you sell products, use custom fields, or upload PDF or Word documents, you’ve probably noticed your visitors can’t find that information via the default WordPress search.</p>\n<p>And, if your visitors can’t find what they’re looking for, they’re going to leave and look elsewhere.</p>\n<p>With poor search results, you’re leaving traffic and revenue on the table.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> is a premium plugin that modifies the WordPress search feature, indexing more of your content so it can create more relevant results.</p>\n<p>Unlike WordPress&#8217; native search, the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP plugin</a> will index and search through your:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>custom fields</li>\n<li>taxonomy terms</li>\n<li>eCommerce product details and descriptions</li>\n<li>content generated by shortcodes</li>\n<li>even PDF, Office, and document content</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With better search results on your website, your users will be able to find the results they need and have a better overall user experience.</p>\n<h3>How to Set Up SearchWP</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> is very easy to set up. It’s designed to be a turnkey search solution that doesn’t need any extensive configuration &#8212; all you need to do is install and activate the plugin.</p>\n<p>(However, there&#8217;re more advanced options available if you’re a developer or want to customize your search results &#8212; more on that below.)</p>\n<p>After installing and activating the plugin, you’ll see a confirmation message. Your content is now being indexed.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1191\" src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-activated.png\" alt=\"SearchWP Review - indexing\" width=\"544\" height=\"90\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-activated.png 544w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-activated-300x50.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s all you need to do! The plugin is now set up and working.</p>\n<p>You can click the <b>view progress and settings</b> link for more information, and to see when its done indexing your content.</p>\n<p>You can also navigate to the settings at <b>Settings &raquo; SearchWP</b>.</p>\n<p>Here, you can customize the priority level to give each aspect of your content in search results, and even <a title=\"How to Exclude Pages from WordPress Search Results\" href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-exclude-pages-from-wordpress-search-results/\" target=\"_blank\">exclude</a> certain types of content.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1192\" src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-weight.png\" alt=\"SearchWP Review - customize\" width=\"977\" height=\"504\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-weight.png 977w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-weight-300x155.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-weight-768x396.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 977px) 100vw, 977px\" /></p>\n<p>You can click the blue <b>Statistics</b> link at the top to view all the searches made on your site.</p>\n<p>For more details on customizing your search results, read the WPBeginner post, <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/improve-wordpress-search-searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\">How to Improve WordPress Search with SearchWP</a>.</p>\n<h3>Supplemental Search Engines</h3>\n<p>What if you want to have different search engines on different areas of your site?</p>\n<p>For example, you might have an FAQ or knowledgebase that you want visitors to be able to search, without random content like blog posts showing up in the results.</p>\n<p>No problem. You can <a title=\"How to Use Multiple Search Forms In WordPress\" href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-use-multiple-search-forms-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">create multiple search forms</a> with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a>.</p>\n<p>At the bottom of the <b>Settings &raquo; SearchWP</b> page, just click the <b>Add New Supplemental Engine</b> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1193\" src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-supplemental.png\" alt=\"SearchWP Review - supplemental\" width=\"940\" height=\"154\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-supplemental.png 940w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-supplemental-300x49.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-supplemental-768x126.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" /></p>\n<p>Check off the things you’d like to index for this type of search, and click the <b>Save Changes</b> button.</p>\n<p>Now, to actually use this search engine on your site, you’ll need to create a specific search form for the supplemental engine. You can check out the <a href=\"https://searchwp.com/docs/kb/supplemental-search-step-by-step/\" target=\"_blank\">SearchWP knowledgebase</a> for a detailed tutorial and code examples on how to do so.</p>\n<p><b>SearchWP Extensions</b></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> also has a number of extensions available to add even more features to your search, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/bbpress/\">bbPress</a> Integration: allow visitors to search through forum threads</li>\n<li>Boolean Search: add support for excluding results based on keywords</li>\n<li>Co-Authors Plus Integration: indexes and searches authors created with Automattic’s <a title=\"How to Credit Multiple Authors (Co-Authors) for Posts in WordPress\" href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/plugins/how-to-credit-multiple-authors-co-authors-for-posts-in-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\">Co-Authors Plus</a> plugin</li>\n<li>FacetWP: adds Amazon-like filtering to any WordPress content listing</li>\n<li>Fuzzy Matches: include search terms that are close in spelling to terms searched</li>\n<li>&#8230;and more</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Documentation and Support</h3>\n<p>Documentation is available on the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP site</a>, including many tutorials with screenshots on how to get started and configure your searches. There’s also help for developers looking to dive deeper into customizing their SearchWP installations, including many hooks and filters.</p>\n<p>Getting support requires purchasing a license (more on that below).</p>\n<p>Once you have your license key, navigate to <b>Settings &raquo; SearchWP</b>, and click on the <b>Help</b> tab at the top. Click the <b>Activate License</b> button at the top, and enter your key.</p>\n<p>You can now open a support ticket right from your dashboard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1194\" src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-help.png\" alt=\"SearchWP Review - support\" width=\"802\" height=\"419\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-help.png 802w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-help-300x157.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/searchwp-review-help-768x401.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 802px) 100vw, 802px\" /></p>\n<h3>License Options</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> offers 3 pricing plans. You can choose depending on the number of sites you want to use SearchWP on. The available plans are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Standard</strong> plan for $79</li>\n<li><strong>Pro</strong> plan for $149</li>\n<li><strong>Pro Plus</strong> plan for $299</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The <strong>Standard</strong> plan is for 1 site, <strong>Pro</strong> is for 5 sites, and <strong>Pro Plus</strong> is for unlimited sites. So, if you’re running a single website, you can sign up with the Standard plan. You can upgrade your plugin license at any time by paying the difference in cost. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/searchwp-pricing.jpg\" alt=\"searchwp-pricing\" width=\"775\" height=\"388\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222666\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/searchwp-pricing.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/searchwp-pricing-300x150.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/searchwp-pricing-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>All licenses include access to all extensions, and 1 year of support and updates. Licenses renew on a yearly basis with a 20% discount. You can purchase a license at any time from the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP site</a>.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> has a 14-day full refund policy so your investment is guaranteed. If you find the plugin not working as advertised or your support ticket remains unresolved, you’ll get your money 100% back. So what’re you waiting for? <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Get started with SearchWP today!</a></p>\n<h3>Bonus Tip: Identify Exactly What Your Visitors are Searching For</h3>\n<p>Once you’ve added search boxes on your site with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a>, you’ll want to see exactly what your visitors are searching for using the search boxes. That’s where <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MonsterInsights</a> comes handy.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-plugin-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-plugin-wordpress\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-221490\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-plugin-wordpress.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-plugin-wordpress-300x135.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-plugin-wordpress-768x347.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a> </p>\n<p>MonsterInsights is the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress and provides you with detailed reports on your site audience and their behavior. Using the plugin, you can track how your site visitors are using the search boxes. </p>\n<p>First, you&#8217;ll need to install the MonsterInsights plugin and <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-google-analytics-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\">set up Google Analytics in your WordPress site</a>. Then, you can go to Google Analytics&#8217; settings and enable site search for your site. Here’s the detailed guide on how to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-set-up-site-search-tracking-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\" target=\"_blank\">set up site search tracking in WordPress using Google Analytics</a>. </p>\n<p>Then, you can see exactly what terms your users are searching on your site by going to <strong>Behavior &raquo; Site Search &raquo; Search Terms</strong> in your Google Analytics profile. This also shows <strong>no results</strong> search terms if there’re any. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/site-search-terms-data-in-Google-Analytics.png\" alt=\"site-search-terms-data-in-Google-Analytics\" width=\"560\" height=\"323\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-222671\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/site-search-terms-data-in-Google-Analytics.png 560w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/site-search-terms-data-in-Google-Analytics-300x173.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Using this site search report, you can identify what your visitors are looking for on your site. Plus, you can discover new keyword ideas for your site.</p>\n<h3>Our Verdict on Using SearchWP to Upgrade Your Default WordPress Search</h3>\n<p>If you’re frustrated by the poor search results on your site, and you’re losing visitors who can’t find what they’re looking for, you need a plugin to improve your WordPress search results.</p>\n<p>We love how easy <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/searchwp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SearchWP</a> is to use, and how it has so many options to configure and customize your searches.</p>\n<p>We give SearchWP 5 out of 5 stars. Here&#8217;s the breakdown of our review scores:</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/searchwp/\">SearchWP Review: Is It the Best WordPress Search Plugin?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:55:\"https://www.isitwp.com/wordpress-plugins/searchwp/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:28:\"https://www.isitwp.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:18:{s:6:\"server\";s:17:\"Sucuri/Cloudproxy\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Tue, 02 Oct 2018 19:46:36 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:11:\"x-sucuri-id\";s:5:\"18003\";s:16:\"x-xss-protection\";s:13:\"1; mode=block\";s:15:\"x-frame-options\";s:10:\"SAMEORIGIN\";s:22:\"x-content-type-options\";s:7:\"nosniff\";s:25:\"strict-transport-security\";a:2:{i:0;s:44:\"max-age=31536000; includeSubdomains; preload\";i:1;s:13:\"max-age=86400\";}s:23:\"content-security-policy\";s:26:\"upgrade-insecure-requests;\";s:10:\"set-cookie\";s:98:\"srv_id=0b5f645014735ca26c59926f73da924b; expires=Tue, 02-Oct-18 19:40:00 GMT; max-age=3600; path=/\";s:4:\"vary\";s:6:\"Cookie\";s:7:\"expires\";s:29:\"Thu, 19 Nov 1981 08:52:00 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:35:\"no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate\";s:6:\"pragma\";s:8:\"no-cache\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"a6cc49d41caa692c70c4ec0783fa9ea9\"\";s:12:\"x-robots-tag\";s:15:\"noindex, follow\";s:9:\"x-backend\";s:22:\"awesomemotive-web2.com\";s:14:\"x-sucuri-cache\";s:3:\"HIT\";}}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20130911040210\";}', 'no');
